Unreleased (private fork fixes)
================================
- rework the 8-ball/9-ball computer player (aiplayer.c): shot candidates
  (pots, soft safeties, one-cushion kick shots when snookered) are now
  played out on a copy of the table with the real physics engine and
  rated with the same foul/win rules evaluate_last_move() applies, so
  the AI no longer banges the cue ball at a random legal ball when no
  clean pot exists. It avoids scratches and wrong-ball fouls, plays
  defensively (leaves the opponent without a pot when it cannot pot
  itself), escapes snookers via the cushions, and chooses a sensible
  cue strength per shot instead of the fixed 0.7. Difficulty (player
  err) still perturbs the chosen direction and strength. billmove.c
  gained BM_simulation_begin()/end() which save/restore the move log
  and mute sounds/ball-trace recording during AI lookahead, plus a
  bounds check in record_move_log_event()
- the AI now also uses real cueing technique: when a pot is found it
  simulates draw/follow/side-english variants of the shot and keeps
  the one that leaves the best position (the chosen cue offset goes
  through the regular queue_point/english path, so spin transfer and
  cushion reaction come from the normal physics). The chosen power is
  shown on the strength bar during the AI's stroke and a cue-ball/
  cross indicator (same graphic as the english control) appears when
  the AI plays with spin
- fix: the player could corrupt an AI shot by rotating the cue view,
  using the english/cue-butt controls or the birdview/freeview aiming
  keys while the AI stroke animation was running. The AI shot (angle,
  elevation, strength, english) is now snapshotted in
  do_computer_move() and restored in queue_shot() right before the
  stroke, and the aiming inputs are ignored while an AI (or network)
  player is at the table
- the physical cue stick is now taken into account when aiming: the
  old ball/cushion clearance check (check_cue) was dead code behind an
  always-off ifdef, so the cue clipped through object balls close
  behind the cue ball and hung inside the cushions. A real geometric
  check (cue_min_Xque, billard.c) computes the lowest elevation at
  which the tapered stick clears all balls and the cushion tops for
  the current aim and english; check_cue() raises the cue above the
  player-chosen elevation when needed and lowers it back when the way
  is free (enforced every frame, for every input path). The elevation
  also feeds the shot physics as before (steeper cue = less forward
  speed, changed spin plane), and playing draw near a rail now forces
  the realistic elevated stroke instead of being silently ignored
- the AI plans with the same constraint: every simulated candidate
  shot is played at the elevation the cue would really need, so shots
  over a blocking ball or away from a rail are planned - and missed or
  made - with the true elevated-stroke physics. Kick-shot escapes got
  a finer aim/strength grid since the cushion rebound depends on speed
- english settings the cue cannot physically be stroked at are now
  rejected for human players too: when no playable elevation exists
  for the requested hit point (cue ball frozen to a rail with draw,
  or a ball frozen right behind the stroke line), check_cue() pulls
  the hit point back towards the centre until the stick clears -
  draw/follow is reduced first, side spin only if that is not enough
  (cue_english_playable(), billard.c). This restores the intent of
  the old dead check_cue() code that used to zero the draw component
  near rails, but based on the real stick geometry: draw near (not
  frozen to) a rail stays available via the visible elevated stroke
- fix broken text entry on non-US keyboard layouts (AZERTY, QWERTZ, ...):
  menu textfields (player name, host, port) relied on the SDL 1.2-era
  keysym->ASCII hack, which mistranslates shifted/layout-remapped
  characters. Printable characters now arrive layout-correct via SDL2
  SDL_TEXTINPUT events while a textfield is edited (handle_text_input(),
  sys_stuff.c; text_input_active(), billard3d.c); game hotkeys still use
  the keydown path and are not delivered twice
- fix VSync swap interval being set before the GL context existed
  (a silent no-op in SDL2); SDL_GL_SetSwapInterval() is now called once
  after SDL_GL_CreateContext(), for both the on and off case
- fix executable self-location (sys_stuff.c enter_data_dir()): gate the
  /proc/<pid>/exe readlink on __linux__ instead of the project-defined
  POSIX macro, NUL-terminate the readlink() result (it is not terminated
  by readlink itself), and make get_data_dir() fall back to "." unless an
  absolute path was found
- drop the SDL 1.2-only SDL_GetWMInfo()/ShowWindow() Windows fullscreen
  hack in sys_fullscreen(); Windows now uses the same SDL2
  SDL_SetWindowFullscreen() path as X11/Wayland, unblocking a future
  Windows build
- update Debian packaging to SDL2: debian/control now Build-Depends on
  libsdl2-dev, libsdl2-net-dev, libsdl2-mixer-dev and libpng-dev instead
  of the EOL SDL 1.2 and libpng12 packages
- update the macOS Xcode project to SDL2: link libSDL2.a instead of the
  vendored libSDL.a 1.2.15, reference homebrew's unversioned lib/ symlinks
  for freetype/libpng/SDL2, and fix the dead mxcl/homebrew clone URL in
  the "Fetch Dependencies" build phase (untested - no Mac available)
- SECURITY: fix a stack buffer overflow when joining a network game: the
  handshake in join_network_game() parsed the two player names from the
  remote peer with unbounded sscanf("%s"), so a hostile/buggy server could
  smash the stack. Names are now read with "%255s" to match the 256-byte
  buffers
- harden the player-name copy macros (strcpy_uscore_2_whtspace /
  strcpy_whtspace_2_uscore, billard3d.h): they now take an explicit
  destination size and never write past it. Previously an over-long
  --name1/--name2 on the CLI or in ~/.foobillardrc overflowed
  player[].name[256] at startup
- harden load_config() (billard3d.c): the config-file reader wrote every
  byte of ~/.foobillardrc into a fixed 20000-byte stack buffer with no
  bounds check; a large or malformed file overflowed the stack on launch.
  The reader now stops at the end of the buffer and warns
- guard getenv("HOME")/getenv("USERPROFILE"): load_config(), save_config()
  (billard3d.c) and init_history() (history.c) used the result in
  strcpy/sprintf into fixed buffers with no NULL check, crashing when the
  variable was unset and overflowing when it was over-long. They now
  NULL-check and use snprintf
- fix menu "VSync ON" being a no-op under SDL2: its body was inside a dead
  "#if SDL_MAJOR_VERSION == 1" block, so selecting it never set
  options_vsync. Both VSync menu entries now use SDL_GL_SetSwapInterval()
- port from SDL 1.2 to SDL2 (Jesse Portnoy): windowing, input, timers,
  SDL2_mixer and SDL2_net; fix default language selection and add the
  missing en-uk manual index
- restore mouse wheel shot-strength adjustment under SDL2: SDL2 reports
  the wheel via SDL_MOUSEWHEEL events instead of button 4/5 presses, so
  sys_stuff.c now translates wheel events (honoring
  SDL_MOUSEWHEEL_FLIPPED) into MOUSE_WHEEL_UP/DOWN_BUTTON events, one
  per notch
- fix balls resting in a pocket jaw (or against a rail) jumping ~1cm to a
  new position between shots: at the shot->next-turn transition
  all_balls_free_place() relocated any ball whose center failed
  in_table_region(), but a ball legally hanging in a pocket mouth (cushion
  cut away) or touching a cushion sits at/past that boundary.
  ball_free_place() now keeps the settled position and only relocates a ball
  that actually overlaps another ball (cue-ball-in-hand placement unchanged);
  pocketing/out-of-bounds are already handled by ball_in_hole /
  remove_balls_from_game
- fix segfault when choosing "Restart Game" from the in-game menu:
  menu_new() never initialized menuEntry->parent_entry, so menu_choose()
  dereferenced an uninitialized/garbage pointer for any ID-type entry
  living directly in the top-level menu (Restart Game, Help, Manual,
  History, Tournament History)
- menu "Restart Game" now calls restart_game() in-process (same as the F10
  shortcut) instead of save_config()+sdl_exit()+execl() re-exec, which was
  fragile and crashed if menu cleanup ran after SDL/GL teardown
- fix strsound() (sound_stuff.c) reading from an uninitialized buffer
  instead of the input filename, and a broken strcmp check that made the
  mp3/ogg extension check always return true
- fix pointer/int comparison warnings against SDL_TimerID (billard3d.c)
- fix format-truncation warnings in history.c date formatting

